Horrific photos from the liberated town close to Kyiv have shown the bodies of dead civilians scattered on its streets. The local mayor said Russian troops had killed his citizens in cold blood. Now local officials have discovered even more evidence of Russian war crimes with this latests terrible discovery. Ukraine's foreign minister demanded further economic measures from the G7 in response to the atrocities. Dymtro Kuleba said: "Bucha massacre was deliberate. Russians aim to eliminate as many Ukrainians as they can. "We must stop them and kick them out. I demand new devastating G7 sanctions NOW." Mr Kuleba proposed an oil, gas and coal embargo, closing all ports to Russian vessels and goods and disconnecting all Russian banks from SWIFT. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UKRAINE UPDATES: